00:20.590 --> 00:23.270
[beeping steadily]

00:29.032 --> 00:30.952
[wheels clattering]

00:30.977 --> 00:33.616
WOMAN [over P.A.]: Dr.
Rose to pediatrics, please.

00:33.617 --> 00:35.656
Dr. Rose to pediatrics.

00:35.657 --> 00:38.457
[sighs]

00:50.337 --> 00:52.377
[indistinct chatter]

00:57.704 --> 00:59.184
Fuck.

01:09.704 --> 01:11.624
- Oh.
- Excuse me. Sorry.

01:13.664 --> 01:14.824
Oh. [Gasps]

01:16.385 --> 01:17.868
What'd you do that for?

01:17.869 --> 01:19.383
You deserved it, that's why!

01:19.384 --> 01:20.663
- You hit me in my mouth!
- That's right.

01:20.664 --> 01:21.671
I hit you right in the mouth.

01:21.672 --> 01:23.143
You're a child abuser!

01:23.144 --> 01:25.297
Please, I want my shirt back,

01:25.415 --> 01:26.574
my watch.

01:26.575 --> 01:27.814
Oh, hi.

01:27.815 --> 01:28.751
Look, guys, this is...

01:28.752 --> 01:29.797
She mugged me two days ago,

01:29.798 --> 01:32.454
took my watch, took my... took my shirt.

01:32.455 --> 01:33.894
[grunting]

01:33.895 --> 01:35.574
- All right, no, no, no, no, no.
- What's happening?

01:35.575 --> 01:37.054
- What's wrong with you?
- My friends are down here.

01:37.055 --> 01:38.694
- And I got... Hey, what...
- He's a child abuser.

01:38.695 --> 01:41.467
Just to be clear, if I step in here,

01:41.492 --> 01:42.375
are you going to arrest me?

01:42.430 --> 01:43.669
Why? Is there a reason I should?

01:43.670 --> 01:45.469
You said I was just helping with inquiries.

01:45.470 --> 01:46.949
I am authorized to make an arrest

01:46.950 --> 01:49.109
if I feel you're in
felony violation of U.S. law.

01:49.110 --> 01:50.269
Well, to my understanding,

01:50.270 --> 01:52.029
FBI agents don't have authority

01:52.030 --> 01:53.149
to make arrests on foreign soil

01:53.150 --> 01:54.429
without consent of the host nation.

01:54.430 --> 01:56.509
Wow, aren't you a big smarty-smarty.

01:56.510 --> 01:58.589
Step in there, I'm on sovereign territory.

01:58.590 --> 02:00.829
Well, I guess you're just
gonna have to roll those dice.

02:00.830 --> 02:02.549
Or you could take your chances with Customs

02:02.550 --> 02:03.950
and Homeland Security.

02:13.030 --> 02:15.070
Wait here.

02:18.150 --> 02:20.510
Interview this guy here.

02:21.550 --> 02:22.790
You remember this guy here?

02:25.510 --> 02:27.989
What did you say to her?

02:27.990 --> 02:30.789
I asked her if there
was an office available.

02:30.790 --> 02:33.309
[reporter speaking
indistinctly on television]

02:33.310 --> 02:34.549
[Tull murmuring]

02:34.550 --> 02:36.069
REPORTER: The victims have
now been identified

02:36.070 --> 02:38.823
as American entrepreneur Aaron Brook

02:38.824 --> 02:40.829
and local woman Coggah Rum.

02:40.830 --> 02:42.909
Mr. Brook was a former
Olympic bronze medalist

02:42.910 --> 02:43.916
for archery.

02:43.941 --> 02:45.830
Both were pronounced dead on the scene.

02:45.830 --> 02:47.549
A police investigation is ongoing.

02:47.550 --> 02:48.709
[indistinct shouting]

02:48.710 --> 02:50.589
Wait! Wait! Wait, I know Jesús!

02:50.590 --> 02:52.149
I'm one of his guys!

02:52.150 --> 02:53.749
[shouting continues]

02:53.750 --> 02:55.189
Help!

02:55.190 --> 02:57.350
[sirens wailing]

02:57.389 --> 03:01.943
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

03:02.088 --> 03:04.088
[life support machine beeping]

03:11.430 --> 03:12.709
Lex: What the...

03:12.710 --> 03:14.029
Where am I?

03:14.030 --> 03:16.629
Wait, I don't have any pants on.

03:16.630 --> 03:18.109
I can't move.

03:18.110 --> 03:20.029
Oh, shit.

03:20.030 --> 03:21.349
There's pizza outside.

03:21.350 --> 03:23.029
Lex: Is she talking to me?

03:23.030 --> 03:25.349
Hey, are you talking to me?

03:25.350 --> 03:27.003
Why can't she hear me?

03:27.004 --> 03:28.789
DOCTOR: Oh, nice. Pizza Island?

03:28.790 --> 03:29.909
NURSE: I think they went

03:29.910 --> 03:30.793
to that new place,

03:30.794 --> 03:32.589
Napoli something-or-other.

03:32.590 --> 03:34.229
DOCTOR: Oh, I've heard they're very good.

03:34.230 --> 03:35.589
Lex: Shouldn't you guys be concentrating

03:35.590 --> 03:36.709
on what you're doing?

03:36.710 --> 03:37.989
He's regaining consciousness.

03:37.990 --> 03:40.189
Lex: I have regained consciousness.

03:40.190 --> 03:41.429
I can hear everything you're saying.

03:41.454 --> 03:43.630
He must have a pretty
strong tolerance for barbiturates.

03:43.630 --> 03:44.690
Lex: Oh, you're judging me now?

03:44.715 --> 03:47.199
You ever been to, uh, Peking Kitchen?

03:47.200 --> 03:48.910
I hear they're supposed to be great.

04:05.110 --> 04:06.950
[birds singing]

04:18.670 --> 04:20.550
♪

04:37.150 --> 04:38.429
Down on the ground now.

04:38.430 --> 04:40.229
Did I say put your hands up?

04:40.230 --> 04:41.549
I said get down on the ground.

04:41.550 --> 04:43.687
Get on the fucking ground now.

04:43.688 --> 04:45.669
Face down.

04:45.670 --> 04:47.709
Hands behind your head.

04:47.710 --> 04:49.789
- [groans]
- Which one are you?

04:49.790 --> 04:51.415
- What do you mean?
- Which one? Your name.

04:51.416 --> 04:53.150
Kransey.

04:54.710 --> 04:56.309
Joel Kransey?

04:56.310 --> 04:57.589
Yeah.

04:57.590 --> 04:59.109
And you're looking for Aaron, right?

04:59.110 --> 05:01.039
Yes.

05:01.040 --> 05:03.367
- Aaron's dead.
- What?

05:03.368 --> 05:04.710
Blown up last night.

05:04.711 --> 05:05.909
Fuck. Fuck.

05:05.910 --> 05:07.509
Who are you?

05:07.510 --> 05:09.629
I'm the only one of his
bosses who said we'd be dumb

05:09.630 --> 05:11.469
to enroll him in the first damn place.

05:11.470 --> 05:14.429
But right now, I'm the
fucking cleaning lady.

05:14.430 --> 05:16.230
- Are you armed?
- No.

05:17.390 --> 05:19.949
All right, get up.

05:19.950 --> 05:21.830
Slowly, slowly.

05:32.193 --> 05:36.149
So she said yes to our invitation?

05:36.150 --> 05:38.750
If she declined, you'd be dead.

05:40.270 --> 05:42.909
I'm sorry, I'm just calling it like it is.

05:42.910 --> 05:45.309
Did she say anything to you?

05:45.310 --> 05:46.629
She wanted me to...

05:46.630 --> 05:49.350
give this-this to Aaron.

06:12.830 --> 06:14.869
Holy...

06:14.870 --> 06:16.749
Fuck.

06:16.750 --> 06:18.509
Do you understand what you did up there?

06:18.510 --> 06:20.550
She said she could get my friends home.

06:25.390 --> 06:27.069
You and I,

06:27.070 --> 06:28.429
we got to go grab lunch.

06:28.430 --> 06:30.669
Cops are gonna be swarming this place.

06:30.670 --> 06:31.670
Come on, let's go, go.

06:31.671 --> 06:33.550
Come on, let's go.

06:38.790 --> 06:40.749
Sit.

06:40.750 --> 06:42.590
[door closes]

06:58.586 --> 07:01.630
What's that now?

07:10.075 --> 07:11.469
Are you a missionary?

07:11.470 --> 07:13.069
It has been brought to my attention

07:13.070 --> 07:15.389
that not everyone who
works here is trustworthy.

07:15.390 --> 07:17.069
Okay.

07:17.070 --> 07:18.909
Look, I've been pretty patient with you,

07:18.910 --> 07:20.709
but honestly, you're starting to rag on me.

07:20.710 --> 07:22.269
I need you to answer some questions,

07:22.270 --> 07:24.630
so let's just stop
tippy-tapping around, okay, fella?

07:25.776 --> 07:28.878
What happened to this woman?

07:35.710 --> 07:37.590
♪

07:38.910 --> 07:40.950
[door opens]

07:42.122 --> 07:43.989
My friends are outside.

07:43.990 --> 07:45.269
Can I see them, please?

07:45.270 --> 07:46.349
Your friends left, sir.

07:47.099 --> 07:48.109
Try and rest.

07:48.110 --> 07:50.509
I'll be back to check on you in a while.

07:50.510 --> 07:52.429
[machines beeping]

07:52.430 --> 07:54.470
[door closes]

07:59.230 --> 08:01.270
[birds singing]

08:08.750 --> 08:09.830
Who's there?

08:14.670 --> 08:16.790
[indistinct chatter]

08:20.950 --> 08:22.949
You're a lucky man.

08:22.950 --> 08:25.029
We'd arrived two minutes later,

08:25.030 --> 08:25.935
and whoosh.

08:25.936 --> 08:27.177
Like a firework.

08:27.232 --> 08:28.469
Yeah.

08:28.470 --> 08:29.489
I'm so lucky.

08:29.490 --> 08:30.630
You're an American?

08:30.631 --> 08:31.749
Mm-hmm.

08:31.750 --> 08:34.275
Why? Is there...

08:34.301 --> 08:35.519
Captain, can I speak to you

08:35.520 --> 08:37.750
for a second?

08:44.630 --> 08:46.869
[line ringing]

08:46.870 --> 08:48.349
- [phone ringing]
- Who is it?

08:48.350 --> 08:49.327
It's, uh, another one of my friends.

08:49.328 --> 08:50.781
It's Cobi. Can-can I...

08:50.782 --> 08:52.709
- Go ahead.
- Thanks.

08:52.710 --> 08:54.309
Hey, how's he doing?

08:54.310 --> 08:55.949
Lex.

08:55.950 --> 08:58.456
Well, why aren't you with him?

08:58.457 --> 09:00.803
What?

09:00.825 --> 09:01.981
Why? For what?

09:04.575 --> 09:06.044
Are you fucking kidding me?

09:07.550 --> 09:08.550
Wait, what do you mean?

09:08.915 --> 09:09.970
Aaron's dead?

09:11.071 --> 09:12.837
How are we gonna get our passports?

09:13.310 --> 09:14.955
You're handling it how?

09:14.980 --> 09:16.025
[line disconnects]

09:16.080 --> 09:18.629
Joel? Joel?

09:18.630 --> 09:20.750
Fuck.

09:23.430 --> 09:24.829
[sighs]

09:24.830 --> 09:26.069
TULL: There are witnesses

09:26.070 --> 09:27.887
to you leaving the embassy with her.

09:27.912 --> 09:29.472
You have security footage?

09:29.473 --> 09:30.536
You don't, right?

09:30.537 --> 09:32.669
So once again, it's just someone's word.

09:32.670 --> 09:34.069
Someone pointing the finger at me.

09:34.070 --> 09:35.949
Okay, I'm interpreting this

09:35.950 --> 09:37.989
as a lack of cooperation.

09:37.990 --> 09:38.938
My lack of Coop...

09:38.939 --> 09:41.229
My lack of cooperation

09:41.230 --> 09:43.732
is because you haven't
afforded me legal representation.

09:43.733 --> 09:44.780
Holy crab apple.

09:45.538 --> 09:47.014
You haven't been offered a lawyer

09:47.015 --> 09:48.201
because you haven't been charged.

09:48.202 --> 09:50.389
Look.

09:50.390 --> 09:52.830
Why don't you just tell
me where these guys are?

10:00.750 --> 10:02.272
Two things. One:

10:02.273 --> 10:03.778
I'm not the type of
guy to give up his friends

10:03.803 --> 10:05.654
- even if there was a reason.
- Right.

10:05.655 --> 10:07.709
And two, are you fucking around?

10:07.710 --> 10:08.789
Can you not see

10:08.790 --> 10:10.190
that these are both me?

10:17.310 --> 10:18.115
[chuckles]

10:18.116 --> 10:19.182
Excuse me.

10:23.508 --> 10:25.828
[sighs]

10:28.789 --> 10:30.230
HOSTESS: Welcome to Pizza Island.

10:32.660 --> 10:34.395
What are we doing here?

10:34.434 --> 10:35.433
Grabbing a pizza.

10:35.434 --> 10:36.636
Go ahead and seat yourself.

10:36.637 --> 10:38.270
See anyone you know?

10:42.670 --> 10:44.350
Let's sit there in the corner.

10:44.971 --> 10:46.080
You can see the room.

10:49.718 --> 10:50.790
WAITRESS: How's the pizza?

11:08.150 --> 11:09.990
[birds chirping]

11:14.454 --> 11:16.054
[panting]

11:25.270 --> 11:26.770
Hi.

11:27.934 --> 11:29.790
[chuckling]: You're not real.

11:30.209 --> 11:31.506
You're dead.

11:31.507 --> 11:32.865
Of course I'm dead.

11:33.780 --> 11:35.309
Am I dead?

11:35.310 --> 11:37.830
Do you think you deserve to live?

11:40.063 --> 11:42.063
I don't think you're
allowed to smoke in here.

11:43.573 --> 11:47.153
You think you can take my
life, and you can still live?

11:47.831 --> 11:49.549
I didn't actually take your life.

11:49.550 --> 11:51.620
Sophia: If you had been in
the same position as Joel,

11:51.621 --> 11:54.989
what would you have done?
Would you have shot me?

11:54.990 --> 11:57.109
Honestly, I think I probably wouldn't have.

11:57.110 --> 11:59.476
Even if you thought I was
about to kill your friends?

12:03.358 --> 12:04.474
You know, I don't know.

12:04.475 --> 12:06.255
Um, I-I'd like to say yes,

12:06.256 --> 12:09.094
but I don't know if I have that in me.

12:09.095 --> 12:11.086
That tells me you
don't care enough to live.

12:11.087 --> 12:12.681
Really?

12:12.682 --> 12:15.390
Well, it tells me that I value life.

12:15.391 --> 12:18.170
I value all life, not just my own.

12:18.171 --> 12:22.248
So... you value your life?

12:22.273 --> 12:23.273
Yes.

12:27.398 --> 12:28.476
Right?

12:33.078 --> 12:34.942
I suppose, if anything...

12:36.598 --> 12:39.041
I probably haven't valued it enough.

12:41.478 --> 12:45.039
Or... I haven't...

12:46.218 --> 12:47.637
respected its value.

12:53.278 --> 12:54.557
Uh... oh.

12:55.425 --> 12:57.118
I forgot they were both there.

12:57.118 --> 12:58.957
I couldn't remember if
he had a goatee or not,

12:58.958 --> 12:59.918
so I asked them to draw two,

12:59.919 --> 13:01.489
one with and one without.

13:02.798 --> 13:04.809
So there are four, not five?

13:07.438 --> 13:09.037
Thank you, Abby.

13:09.038 --> 13:10.837
It's definitely him, though.

13:10.838 --> 13:12.717
What did you do with her?

13:12.718 --> 13:14.037
Leave her in a ditch?

13:14.038 --> 13:15.437
Did you all just have your way with...?

13:15.438 --> 13:16.838
Thank you, Abby.

13:25.478 --> 13:28.677
So we're clear that you've
been positively identified.

13:28.678 --> 13:30.597
I'm clear that I'm being singled out, yeah.

13:30.598 --> 13:31.790
Oh, you're the victim.

13:31.791 --> 13:33.079
Gus: That's not what I'm saying.

13:33.080 --> 13:35.437
Oh, there I was thinking that the
missing girl was the victim.

13:35.438 --> 13:37.357
Are you implying that we somehow
harmed this young lady?

13:37.358 --> 13:38.797
No, I'm not saying you did anything to her,

13:38.798 --> 13:40.357
but I do believe you know her whereabouts.

13:40.358 --> 13:41.677
And I don't buy for a minute

13:41.678 --> 13:42.997
that you're protecting your friends.

13:42.998 --> 13:44.437
I think you're protecting yourself.

13:44.438 --> 13:45.938
Man.

13:47.318 --> 13:49.397
Only if you knew how wrong you are.

13:49.398 --> 13:51.317
Know what's crazy?

13:51.318 --> 13:52.957
My entire adult life,

13:52.958 --> 13:54.757
I've been taking this kind of shit

13:54.758 --> 13:56.237
for what other people have done.

13:56.238 --> 13:57.917
Why are you even investigating me?

13:57.918 --> 13:59.277
For the last week,

13:59.278 --> 14:02.117
I have literally been running for my life.

14:02.118 --> 14:04.051
I've been threatened, I've been chased.

14:05.318 --> 14:08.077
I've been attacked, I've been blown up!

14:08.078 --> 14:11.868
And somehow I end up
being the one investigated.

14:11.869 --> 14:14.345
Serious crimes have gone down here.

14:14.346 --> 14:16.477
Crimes against me!

14:16.478 --> 14:19.597
And now you want me to cooperate with you.

14:20.318 --> 14:22.117
While I'm sitting here looking at you,

14:22.118 --> 14:23.597
knowing that you're looking at me

14:23.598 --> 14:25.204
as if I'm the fucking criminal.

14:25.933 --> 14:27.198
[Gus sighs]

14:28.512 --> 14:31.277
That girl's parents
call the embassy every hour.

14:31.278 --> 14:33.956
Every hour of every day.

14:34.676 --> 14:36.637
Now, don't you think a parent
has a basic right

14:36.638 --> 14:37.918
to know where their child is?

14:40.478 --> 14:41.997
I was on annual leave in the Caribbean

14:41.998 --> 14:43.317
when I got the call to mop up.

14:43.318 --> 14:45.197
Sorry I screwed up your vacation.

14:45.198 --> 14:46.317
"Vacation." Yeah, right.

14:46.318 --> 14:47.250
I was under the impression

14:47.251 --> 14:48.677
this whole thing was a bust.

14:48.678 --> 14:50.437
I mean, giving her a jacket?

14:50.438 --> 14:51.438
Seriously?

14:52.962 --> 14:54.077
Who killed Aaron?

14:54.078 --> 14:55.717
Paris: It's too early to say.

14:55.718 --> 14:57.517
The point of us setting up front businesses

14:57.518 --> 14:59.557
is for our ops to hide in plain sight.

14:59.558 --> 15:00.682
The moment you become.

15:00.683 --> 15:02.797
Central America's second biggest
Tilapia exporter,

15:02.798 --> 15:04.197
you're not exactly under the radar.

15:04.198 --> 15:05.677
The fucking egomaniac.

15:05.678 --> 15:08.037
So you think he was whacked
by a rival fish farmer.

15:08.038 --> 15:09.357
HOSTESS: Welcome to Pizza Island.

15:09.358 --> 15:10.437
Paris: Yeah, something like...

15:10.438 --> 15:12.078
Something like that.

15:17.198 --> 15:18.598
Is that them?

15:19.758 --> 15:21.158
It is them, right?

15:22.918 --> 15:24.517
All right, so here's what I need you to do.

15:24.518 --> 15:26.917
I want you to go over
there and positively I.D. them

15:26.918 --> 15:28.678
as the drug dealers from the boat.

15:30.198 --> 15:32.397
What's gonna happen to them if I do?

15:32.398 --> 15:34.358
What do you think is gonna happen?

15:42.118 --> 15:45.917
You're asking me to be complicit
in ending their lives.

15:45.918 --> 15:47.477
Says the man who shot a cop.

15:47.478 --> 15:48.677
I had no fucking choice.

15:48.678 --> 15:49.997
She would have killed all of us.

15:49.998 --> 15:51.557
You made a pact up there.

15:51.558 --> 15:53.197
Now, for this to work,

15:53.198 --> 15:55.117
she has to be the only game in town.

15:55.118 --> 15:56.317
That was her counteroffer.

15:56.318 --> 15:57.505
And you have to kill them?

15:57.506 --> 15:59.157
With your plausible accountability.

15:59.158 --> 16:00.197
Now, go over there.

16:00.198 --> 16:01.685
Be 100% sure that it's them,

16:01.686 --> 16:03.036
because right now we are firmly

16:03.037 --> 16:04.957
in the "no more fucking mistakes" zone.

16:04.958 --> 16:06.357
And if it is them,

16:06.358 --> 16:08.477
I want you to put both hands on the table

16:08.478 --> 16:10.518
and strike up a conversation.

16:16.358 --> 16:18.009
If I do this,

16:19.238 --> 16:21.477
will you guarantee my friends get home?

16:21.478 --> 16:24.197
I can't guarantee you anything.

16:24.198 --> 16:26.597
But what I can guarantee is
that if you don't deliver

16:26.598 --> 16:28.077
on your promise to our
friend in the mountain,

16:28.078 --> 16:30.118
things go very, very bad.

16:33.918 --> 16:35.958
You mind if we move this along?

16:47.369 --> 16:49.303
What should I talk to them about?

16:58.518 --> 17:00.518
♪

17:22.117 --> 17:23.877
Excu-Excuse me.

17:23.877 --> 17:25.317
Uh, the Hummingbird Highway,

17:25.318 --> 17:27.964
does-does... does that go
all the way to Belmopan?

17:27.965 --> 17:29.437
I'm sorry?

17:29.438 --> 17:30.518
You look familiar.

17:39.249 --> 17:42.957
'Cause, uh, I-I wasn't sure
if it was the, uh... that

17:42.958 --> 17:44.677
or the-the... the George Price Highway.

17:44.678 --> 17:45.917
The boat.

17:45.918 --> 17:47.089
You were on the boat.

17:47.090 --> 17:48.561
Agnes: What are you doing?

17:53.957 --> 17:56.718
Being seen together is not smart.

17:58.118 --> 18:00.038
Are these your friends?

18:04.786 --> 18:06.437
Walk away.

18:06.438 --> 18:08.318
♪

18:10.011 --> 18:11.998
Walk out the door.

